calibration status
In the forward bias, gain of the HBD GEMs are often (or always?) set to low 
to prevent freaquent discharge leading to the dead short of GEMs.
The gain calibration using scintillation photons can not be performed in this low gain operation,
because It is hard to distinguish the signal induced by a scintillation photon from noise.
So, this file describes if the operation gain is low or not.
0 -> normal operation
1 -> low gain operation
